sentences: His first chance at being with a "made band" was in 1993 when Gaby Hauke (Accept fame) called up Bormann to ask if he was interested in joining Bonfire.
His time with the band was short lived as the band went their separate ways in 1994.
Bormann carried on with Jaded Heart while still maintaining involvement in other projects until 2004.
He was nominated for a few categories for the 50th and 51st Grammy Awards in 2008 and 2009.

In 2013, after working together in the band The Sygnet (from 1997 to 2000), Bormann joined guitarist Alex Beyrodt and drummer André Hilgers in the band Silent Force replacing previous vocalist D.C. Cooper.

In 2013, after working together in the band The Sygnet (from 1997 to 2000), Bormann joined guitarist Alex Beyrodt and drummer André Hilgers in the band Silent Force replacing previous vocalist D.C. Cooper.
The first Silent Force album with Bormann as vocalist is called Rising From Ashes and was released in 2013.
2001: German Rock Stars – Wings Of Freedom
2003: Biss – Joker in the Deck
2004: 20th Century Boys – Beware of the Rex!
2006: Michael Bormann – Conspiracy
2010: Michael Bormann – Different
2014: Michael Bormann - Love Is Magic
2019: Michael Bormann´s Jaded Hard - Feels Like Yesterday
Worth noting, Bormann and ex-Bonfire mate Angel Schleifer reunited three years later as Charade.

Through the years, Bormann has worked with noted musicians such as J.R. Blackmore (son of Ritchie Blackmore of Deep Purple and Rainbow), Jochen 'Zeno' Roth (brother of Uli John Roth of Scorpions fame), Jos Zoomer (from Vandenberg) and Anette Blyckert of Alyson Avenue and Nightwish.
